summary: Being member of Tywin Lannister’s ward and you two falling for the other would include
title: Being member of Tywin Lannister’s ward and you two falling for the other would include
body:
( GIF Credit [ X ] )

- You being such a good warrior that no one could doubt it even from a moment when you join the Lannisters ward.

- Him discovering you one morning when you are training in the courtyard, beating the asses of all the fools who dare to attack you, and being really impressed of your skills, and even more impressed when he realises you are a woman.

- Him promoting you to his personal ward, supposedly to have the better sword of his ward protecting him directly, but really doing it to keep you near him and to know you a bit better, because he find you amazing.

- Him going anywhere, if not in your company, and trying to spend with you the most time he can, so he starts bringing you to his war councils, to his feasts and to his private rooms, especially if he is working on something or just relaxing a bit, far from the world.

- Him being kind with you all times, even in front of other persons, and you feeling really impressed and honoured, because you know that Lord Lannister is not well knowed for his kindness.

- His sons and daughter starting to feel that something strange happens between you two when they saw how soft and kind he is treating you, and him hinting them nothing, even dismissing them from his presence if any of them dare to say that he have a soft spot on you.

- Tyrion finally warning you about his father, just because he doesn’t want you to end hurted by his -more than occasional- rage, and you having to promise him that everything is fine with him and you, and that he had to worry not.

- Cersei constantly remembering you that you are not enough woman for his father, not by born, neither by your actual position, trying to keep you out her family as much as she can.

- Jaime not being sure if he likes the idea of his father taking a lover, and keeping always an eye over you to know if you are interested really on gain his father’s heart or his wallet.

- Him promising you that you should fear nothing of his sons or his daughter, because no one of them would dare to hurt you if he is near, hinting you to stay with him as much as you can and not leaving his company for your own sake.

- Him subtly caressing your hand when he catches something you had on your own, looking you sharply in the eye and smirking, leaving all to your understanding in the most subtle way.

- Him finally confessing you that he is starting to feel deep and strong things for you, but menacing you subtly with any kind of punishment if you don’t reciprocate his feelings, and you -not as subtly as he is- just entwining your fingers with hims and promising him you will keep his secret, as much as he keeps yours.

tags: my baby dragon is a man now
summary:
THIS SCENE.
Maester Aemon. The OG, now and always. He’s mischievous. He’s a wiseass. He’s adorable. HE BELIEVES IN THIS...
body:
THIS SCENE.

Maester Aemon. The OG, now and always. He’s mischievous. He’s a wiseass. He’s adorable. HE BELIEVES IN THIS BOY.

Whether he KNEW or not (he totally fucking knew), he had so much of a role in shaping Jon.

I miss him so much.

And look at Jon’s face, a minute ago he’s like STFU Sam, but he’s thirsty for this. He just needs someone to show they believe in him (he did get that from the LC, but he was still a steward). Also, he is relieved that he doesn’t have to live under Thorne’s command. But mostly it’s like, “This oldass motherfucking dragon who could have been king of the whole damn thing thinks I will be the best leader. That’s awesome!”


Aemon’s sitting back like a proud granddad. Jon’s proud and humbled. Somewhere above, Ned Stark and Prince Baegar are beaming with pride because if no one is gonna tell the boy he’s actually the rightful king, at least he can be the biggest shield guarding the realms of men.


Here’s to you, Maester Aemon, and you, King Crow!

caption:
Sky Atlantic’s Game of Thrones: Greatest Moments (2018)

11. Jon Snow’s True Parentage & Incest (S7, Ep.7)

“Robert’s Rebellion was built on a lie. Rhaegar didn’t kidnap my aunt or rape her. He loved her. And she loved him. And Jon… Jon’s real name…”

“His name is Aegon Targaryen. You have to protect him. Promise me, Ned.”

“He’s never been a bastard. He’s the heir to the Iron Throne. He needs to know. We need to tell him.”

- Brandon Stark and Lyanna Stark

10. Ramsay Bolton’s Death (S6, Ep.9)

“Your words will disappear. Your house will disappear. Your name will disappear. All memory of you will disappear.”

- Sansa Stark
